WEBVTT

00:00:01.647 --> 00:00:04.025 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
On April 20, 2017,

00:00:04.025 --> 00:00:07.279 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
the Supreme Court
of the Russian Federation criminalized

00:00:07.279 --> 00:00:09.491 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
the activity of Jehovah’s Witnesses.

00:00:12.453 --> 00:00:15.081 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
As of July 4, 2019,

00:00:15.081 --> 00:00:18.961 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
authorities have progressively
seized 131 of the properties

00:00:18.961 --> 00:00:21.506 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
owned by Jehovah’s Witnesses,

00:00:21.506 --> 00:00:24.176 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
with an additional 60 properties
subject to confiscation.

00:00:24.176 --> 00:00:26.178 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
One of the seized properties

00:00:26.178 --> 00:00:28.222 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
was the former
Russia branch complex in Solnechnoye.

00:00:30.934 --> 00:00:33.562 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
At the time of filming,
the Russian authorities continue

00:00:33.562 --> 00:00:36.733 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
their aggressive attack
on Jehovah’s Witnesses.

00:00:36.733 --> 00:00:39.486 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
As of August 17, 2020,

00:00:39.486 --> 00:00:42.407 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
there were 42 Witnesses
who were in pretrial detention

00:00:42.407 --> 00:00:44.785 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
or sentenced to prison,

00:00:44.785 --> 00:00:47.830 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
32 who were under house arrest,

00:00:47.830 --> 00:00:51.209 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and 169 who were not allowed
to leave their hometown.

00:00:51.209 --> 00:00:53.879 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
All have been charged with organizing,

00:00:53.879 --> 00:00:56.508 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
participating in, or financing the activity

00:00:56.508 --> 00:00:59.053 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
of a so-called “extremist” organization.

00:01:00.304 --> 00:01:04.267 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
At least 380 Witnesses were,
at the time, under investigation

00:01:04.267 --> 00:01:08.272 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
—ranging in age from 19 to 89 years old.

00:01:09.149 --> 00:01:11.985 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
What has this meant
for the individuals affected?

00:01:11.985 --> 00:01:13.613 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
As an example,

00:01:13.613 --> 00:01:15.990 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
on June 3, 2018,

00:01:15.990 --> 00:01:19.495 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
Brother Sergey Klimov was arrested.

00:01:19.495 --> 00:01:21.497 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
Local authorities initiated

00:01:21.497 --> 00:01:23.333 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
criminal charges against him,

00:01:23.333 --> 00:01:26.337 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
placing him
in pretrial detention for two months.

00:01:26.337 --> 00:01:29.591 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
This detention was extended seven times,

00:01:29.591 --> 00:01:31.593 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
separating him from his wife and family

00:01:31.593 --> 00:01:33.763 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
for a year and five months,

00:01:33.763 --> 00:01:36.182 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
before he was finally tried and sentenced.

00:01:37.559 --> 00:01:39.562 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
On November 5, 2019,

00:01:39.562 --> 00:01:42.983 line:10%,start position:50%,center align:center
he was sentenced to six years in prison.

00:01:47.572 --> 00:01:49.699 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Two of our dear young people in Russia,

00:01:49.699 --> 00:01:52.703 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Brother Yegor Baranov
and Sister Darya Dulova,

00:01:52.703 --> 00:01:54.998 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
are courageously facing criminal conviction

00:01:54.998 --> 00:01:57.334 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and potential long-term imprisonment.

00:01:58.669 --> 00:02:01.381 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Brother Baranov is only 19 years old.

00:02:01.381 --> 00:02:06.220 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
When the authorities raided her home,
Sister Dulova was only 18 years old.

00:02:08.556 --> 00:02:10.767 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
By means of the Newsroom on jw.org,

00:02:10.767 --> 00:02:13.104 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
we are informed of updated news events.

00:02:13.104 --> 00:02:15.106 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
This page includes links to name lists

00:02:15.106 --> 00:02:17.776 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
of Witnesses
currently imprisoned for their faith,

00:02:17.776 --> 00:02:21.114 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
which can help us include
them specifically in our prayers.

00:02:21.990 --> 00:02:25.286 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Our brothers and sisters in Russia
are resolved to remain loyal to Jehovah

00:02:25.286 --> 00:02:27.956 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
despite any opposition,

00:02:27.956 --> 00:02:30.542 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
and they put their confidence
in him in the assurance

00:02:30.542 --> 00:02:33.379 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
that Jehovah is on their side!

